<subSubSection lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1689,2041]" lastBlockId="28.[151,1437,152,648]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1833,1860]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Integument with larger, rounded papillae each surrounded by a collar of smaller, irregular ones (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1614,1639]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,180,1586]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,174,1595]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–c. H. amoenoderma, female (MD 097); a. integument papillae; b. palp; c. coxal and genital field; d.–g. H. poseidon female (MNHN B 16 C); d. integument papillae; e. Cx-I+II; f. III-L-4–6 (detail. trident setae at higher magnification); g. IV-L-4–6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613330/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Figs 14 d</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[215,290,1869,1897]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1596,1621]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,661,1576]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,661,1576]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 15. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–d. H. amoenoderma, female (MD 151); a. Cx-I+II; b.–d. integument papillae in various views. e.–h. H. poseidon; e. Cx-I+II; f.–h. integument papillae in various views. i.–m. H. sp. inc. nr. lasioderma (MD 061); i. Cx-I+II; k.–m. integument papillae in various views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613332/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
15 f 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[259,273,1870,1896]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
h
</figureCitation>
). Medial margin of Cx-I with distinct projections associated with setal bases (
<figureCitation box="[1164,1270,1870,1897]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1614,1639]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,180,1586]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,174,1595]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–c. H. amoenoderma, female (MD 097); a. integument papillae; b. palp; c. coxal and genital field; d.–g. H. poseidon female (MNHN B 16 C); d. integument papillae; e. Cx-I+II; f. III-L-4–6 (detail. trident setae at higher magnification); g. IV-L-4–6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613330/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Figs 14 e</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1283,1333,1869,1897]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1596,1621]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,661,1576]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,661,1576]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 15. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–d. H. amoenoderma, female (MD 151); a. Cx-I+II; b.–d. integument papillae in various views. e.–h. H. poseidon; e. Cx-I+II; f.–h. integument papillae in various views. i.–m. H. sp. inc. nr. lasioderma (MD 061); i. Cx-I+II; k.–m. integument papillae in various views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613332/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">15 e</figureCitation>
). Genital field with very numerous Ac (100 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[537,551,1906,1932]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
180 pairs, maximum n per transect, 7 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[976,990,1906,1932]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
12); sexual dimorphism in genital plate setae number and density: 
<specimenCount box="[445,487,1943,1969]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="male">♂♂</specimenCount>
50 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[520,534,1942,1968]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
70 (ratio n/plate L 0.20 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[787,801,1942,1968]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
0.28), 
<specimenCount box="[872,914,1943,1969]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="female">♀♀</specimenCount>
35 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[948,962,1942,1968]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
50 (ratio 0.14 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1111,1125,1942,1968]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
0.16). Leg segments slender (e.g., L/H ratio I-L-5, 4.5 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[438,452,1978,2004]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
6.1; II-L-5, 5.9 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[622,636,1978,2004]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
7.3; III-L-5, 5.0 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[815,829,1978,2004]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
7.0; IV-L-5, 6.5 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1007,1021,1978,2004]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
8.4). Distal edges of I-IV-L-4-5 with thickened, bi- or trifurcated setae, particularly strongly developed and trident-shaped at III-L-5 (
<figureCitation box="[1236,1337,2014,2041]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1614,1639]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,180,1586]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,174,1595]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–c. H. amoenoderma, female (MD 097); a. integument papillae; b. palp; c. coxal and genital field; d.–g. H. poseidon female (MNHN B 16 C); d. integument papillae; e. Cx-I+II; f. III-L-4–6 (detail. trident setae at higher magnification); g. IV-L-4–6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613330/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 14 f</figureCitation>
); ventral setae of IV-L-4-5 elongated; swimming setae (anterior/posterior) II-L-5, 0/1; III-L-4, 0/9-13; III-L-5, 0/6-9; IV-L- 4, 6-12/6-11; IV-L-5, 0[-1]/5-8; claw length (all legs) 23-30; L ratio claw/ I-IV-L-5, 6-13 [mean: 8] % (see 
<figureCitation box="[1356,1436,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1614,1639]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,180,1586]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,174,1595]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–c. H. amoenoderma, female (MD 097); a. integument papillae; b. palp; c. coxal and genital field; d.–g. H. poseidon female (MNHN B 16 C); d. integument papillae; e. Cx-I+II; f. III-L-4–6 (detail. trident setae at higher magnification); g. IV-L-4–6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613330/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
f-g).
</paragraph>
